import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data['route'].value_counts().reset_index()
    route_counts.columns = ['route', 'count']
    top_routes = route_counts.head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='route', y='count', data=top_routes, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.set(xlabel='Route', ylabel='Number of Flights')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    for i, v in enumerate(top_routes['count']):
        ax.text(i, v + 50, str(v), color='black', ha='center')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports are the most popular?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
